  "description": "Perennial shrubby pepper (Capsicum frutescens, 90–120+ days to first fruit) producing small upright intensely pungent fruit (50,000–175,000 SHU). Native to tropical Americas, dispersed to Africa via Portuguese colonial networks; name from Bantu meaning \"pepper-pepper.\" Requires warm climate (zones 9–11); grows as ornamental in cooler zones. Self-compatible; single plant produces fruit. Compact, heavily-branched growth; suitable for containers and small spaces. Prolific and decorative.",
